            "heading": undefined,
            "content": "Arch’s structure makes it possible to execute the multi-party contracts necessary for Liquidity Pools (LPs), which are foundational to building the Automated Market Makers (AMMs) that drive trust-minimized DEXs. These liquidity pools serve as an instant, permissionless source of liquidity from multiple sources, which borrowers can tap into without relying on DLCs or order books managed off-chain."
