            "heading": "leader-selection",
            "content": "The block production process in our dPoS consensus begins with leader selection, which operates on a predetermined schedule for each epoch or fixed time period. Leaders are strategically selected based on their stake weight in the network, creating a deterministic schedule that's transparent and known to all participating validators. To maintain system reliability, multiple backup leaders are designated for each slot, providing essential fault tolerance should the primary leader fail to produce a block within the allocated time frame."
